SIMPLE: assortment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Assortment
<hw>As*sort"ment</hw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>assortiment</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act of assorting, or
distributing into sorts, kinds, or classes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection or quantity of things distributed into
kinds or sorts; a number of things assorted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A collection containing a variety of sorts or kinds
adapted to various wants, demands, or purposes; <as>as, an
<ex>assortment</ex> of goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assot</ent>⟦br⟧
